Wfuzz
Web application fuzzer for finding hidden content

Web Application
Description
Wfuzz is a flexible web fuzzer used to brute force web application parameters, discover hidden directories, files, and test for various vulnerabilities.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which wfuzz
Install command:

sudo apt install wfuzz
Basic Syntax
wfuzz -w <wordlist> <URL/FUZZ>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
wfuzz -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt http://target.com/FUZZ

Directory bruteforce	Find hidden directories	
wfuzz -w wordlist.txt -d "user=FUZZ&pass=test" http://target.com/login

POST parameter fuzzing	Test login parameters	
wfuzz -w wordlist.txt --hc 404 http://target.com/FUZZ

Hide 404 responses	Filter out not found pages	
wfuzz -w wordlist.txt -H "Cookie: session=FUZZ" http://target.com/

Header fuzzing	Test header values	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Choose appropriate wordlist
2
Replace fuzz point with FUZZ keyword
3
Run wfuzz with options
4
Filter unwanted responses with --hc/--hl/--hw
5
Analyze interesting responses
Understanding the Output
Shows response code, lines, words, chars for each payload. Use filters to focus on valid responses.

Important Warnings
•
High request volume can trigger WAF
•
Use rate limiting with -t option
•
Only test authorized targets
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
